Subject: Re: [T2] cylinder head temp sender installation

>  Andrew Mueller wrote:
> > on my second cylinder head temp sender unit, the kind
> > that goes around the number 3 spark plug.  broke the
> > first installing, it seems really fragile to me.
> > anyone have any hints on how to make this thing last a
> > while>  THANKS

Andrew

I open the sender up a bit with a small file...it doesn't ake much effort to make that hole in the
crimp connector a little larger,  so it slips on the plug easily. Also, you can put a small notch
in the tin to place the wire in while using the plug  socket so the socket doesn't pinch the wire

